description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Staff Nurse - Band 5&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Savernake Community Hospital - Chestnut Ward&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Various Hours Available – Full and Part-Time Opportunities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Wiltshire Health and Care are looking for Registered Nurses to join our friendly team on Chestnut Ward at Savernake Community Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We recognise that our staff are our most valuable resource and are proud of the excellent levels of service our organisation provides to our service users through our dedicated and conscientious workforce. With this in mind, we offer a range of staff benefits including:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent annual leave entitlement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to the NHS Pension Scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free parking on most of our sites&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS discounts and salary sacrifice schemes via our Employee Benefit Portal ‘Vivup’&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Training and development pathways&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible working opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We can currently offer full and part time hours across a three shift patterned roster.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidates will need to demonstrate a compassionate and caring approach to their care delivery, working with patients who have undergone surgery or been medically unwell to support their rehabilitation. They should also have a genuine interest in nursing older people who may need encouragement to meet their full potential in order to return to their own homes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post offers an opportunity to gain experience in wound care, management of multiple medical co-morbidities and complex discharge planning and would be suitable for an experienced or newly qualified nurse looking to be part of a small team of enthusiastic and committed staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Wiltshire is a perfect mix of beautiful rural countryside and quaint historic towns and villages, whilst being within easy reach of the hustle and bustle of nearby cities. Savernake Hospital is perfectly placed in the beautiful market town of Marlborough. It has extensive grounds and free car parking on site for staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal visits to the hospital are very much encouraged. Please contact the ward on01672 517243 for further information or to arrange an informal visit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;*this role is eligible for a recruitment and retention premium of £3000, paid in 2 instalments – £1500 following successful probation period completion (6months) and £1500 following one years’ service.&lt;/p&gt;
